Package: taskbar-monitor
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.8),
 python3-gi,
 gir1.2-gtk-3.0,
 gir1.2-ayatanaappindicator3-0.1 | gir1.2-appindicator3-0.1
Maintainer: Marllon Gomes <marllon.fgomes@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/MarllonGomes/TaskbarMonitor
Description: Minimalist hardware monitor in the top bar
 TaskbarMonitor shows CPU, GPU, RAM, disk and network load and temperature in
 the top bar, with a detailed dropdown. On GNOME (Ubuntu) it is a native Shell
 extension with compact panel groups, usage meters and temperature badges; on
 other desktops it runs as an AppIndicator tray app. It updates once a second.
 .
 All readings come from /proc and /sys (and nvidia-smi for NVIDIA GPUs), so it
 runs as a normal user with no root privileges and no kernel module — unlike
 the Windows build, CPU and disk temperatures need no special driver on Linux.
